# receive.link routing. NO "/*" catch-all (it shadows real assets: /dist/*.js + /style.css would all
# serve an HTML page, breaking every bundle). Real assets serve themselves; the marketing homepage
# owns "/"; unknown paths 404. The back-half receiver pages in the new design (web/result/index.html)
# own /confirm (reveal), /revoke, /qr -- home-result.ts routes by location.pathname, so the URL MUST stay
# /confirm etc. The target MUST be "/result/" WITH the trailing slash: "/result" (no slash) is a directory
# that Cloudflare 308-redirects to "/result/", which changes the URL and collapses all three routes to one
# pathname (silently breaking /revoke + /qr). Same reason "/" targets "/home/". The app (app.html -> clean
# URL /app, a FILE so no slash needed) still owns the sender upload /u (a share-link open /#code is bounced
# to /u client-side, code staying in the hash) and the receiver download /d/<id>.
/confirm   /result/  200
/revoke    /result/  200
/qr        /result/  200
/d/*       /receive/ 200
/u         /send/    200
/account   /account/ 200
/          /home/    200
